        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 1:21PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 120 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Black Forest, or 14 miles northeast of Colorado Springs, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colorado Springs, Air Force Academy, Calhan, Black Forest, Peyton,
Falcon, and Cimarron Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
